Subject: Navier-Stokes Pressure-Coupling Inequality Boundary Ledger

Description: Project-local ledger for testing whether pressure and strain-vorticity coupling can become a one-sided continuation-scale inequality.

& [NavierStokesPressureCouplingInequalityBoundaryLedger] is a math inquiry tool
  + [tool_uuid] is 95e04c9a-44a6-4faf-8a11-96886004d552
  + [project] is seven math problems
  + [problem] is Navier-Stokes Existence and Smoothness
  + [created_at] is 2026-06-26T19:33Z
  + [trigger_record] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\proof_inquiry\2026-06-26_navier_stokes_full_strain_coupling_term_map_001.sop
  + [role] is distinguish plausible full-equation counteraction from a proof-relevant one-sided inequality
  + [not_role] is proving Navier-Stokes, asserting pressure coercivity, or turning criteria into estimates

& [ColumnSet] is the inequality-boundary surface
  + [candidate_bound] is the proposed inequality shape or term grouping
  + [left_side] is the controlled quantity or defect
  + [right_side] is the amplifying term, dissipative term, pressure-coupling term, or continuation-scale norm
  + [sign_requirement] is negative_control, absorbable_positive_part, cancellation, conditional, or unknown
  + [scale_requirement] is critical_or_continuation_level, subcritical, energy_level, local, or unclear
  + [available_status] is known_identity, criterion, perturbative_estimate, turbulence_diagnostic, conjectural, or absent
  + [boundary_result] is inside_candidate, boundary_only, outside_proof, or deep_research_needed
  + [first_missing_feature] is the earliest missing mathematical feature

& [UseProcedure] is the boundary-ledger workflow
  + [step_001_name_bound] is write the inequality shape and controlled quantity
  + [step_002_check_sign] is test whether pressure/coupling terms have definite sign, absorbability, or cancellation
  + [step_003_check_scale] is test whether the inequality acts at critical or continuation scale
  + [step_004_check_availability] is classify whether the relation is an identity, estimate, criterion, diagnostic, conjecture, or absent
  + [step_005_update_lock_mass] is reduce sign/coercivity lock only for a valid one-sided estimate

  = must: reject redistribution without sign as proof progress
  = must: reject criteria that assume the target control
  = should: preserve pressure and strain-vorticity terms as high-value periphery when sign is unknown
  - never: count turbulence diagnostics as deterministic regularity estimates

